            <thetext>There are lots of stdout and stderr redirections to /dev/null in the Makefiles and although this makes the output nice and shiny, its difficult to see why make exits with an error message like this:

make: *** [all] Error 127

i would suggest to
1. check for all necessary tools before performing any actions and inform the user in case one or more are missing
2. redirect all error messages to some file and show it in case an error occures (check exit values of all commands)</thetext>
